    <prp:code/>
    <prp:abstract>tau Ceti is the nearest G-type star (3.65 pc) that harbours both a debris disk and planets, with 5 known super Earths tightly nestled inside 1.5 AU. It appears to be a close analog to our Solar System, except that it is missing giant planets on wider orbits, though because of observational biases, if there were any they would not have yet been detected. We propose to use ALMA to image the inner edge of tau Ceti's disk and infer the presence of an unseen massive planet that could be clearing the central hole in the resolved disk.</prp:abstract>
